opendial.domains.rules.effects

Class TemplateEffect

  • java.lang.Object
    • opendial.domains.rules.effects.BasicEffect
      • opendial.domains.rules.effects.TemplateEffect

  • public final class TemplateEffect
extends BasicEffect
    Representation of a basic effect of a rule. A basic effect is formally defined as a triple with:
    1. a (possibly underspecified) variable label;
    2. one of four basic operations on the variable SET, DISCARD, ADD;
    3. a (possibly underspecified) variable value;

      • TemplateEffect

        public TemplateEffect(Template variable,
                      Template value,
                      int priority,
                      boolean exclusive,
                      boolean negated)
        Constructs a new effect, with a variable label, value, and other arguments. The argument "add" specifies whether the effect is mutually exclusive with other effects. The argument "negated" specifies whether the effect includes a negation.
        Parameters:
        variable - variable label
        value - variable value
        priority - the priority level (default is 1)
        exclusive - whether distinct values are mutually exclusive or not
        negated - whether to negate the effect or not.
